basic.floral_language:
Viburnum nudum 'Brandywine' 
Floriography: beautiful, fortune, perseverant
Viburnum nudum 'Brandywine' is a deciduous shrub with grayish green, broadly ovate leaves covered by small hairs. Flowers nearly hemispherical shape, cute and exquisite, in flowering seasons, the plant is covered by numerous vigorous and vivid flowers. Often used as ornamental flowers and trees for landscaping or home decoration.
Viburnum nudum 'Brandywine' likes sunshine, also shade-tolerant. Flowers in May-June for 1-2 weeks.
basic.blooming: Flowering period May-June, viewing period 1-2 weeks
basic.color: Turn to red in autumn, flower color white or yellow
